        </center>
    </h2>
    <p>
        <center>
            Level 3 Access to Higher Education courses are designed to enable mature learners (19+) 
            who have been out of education to gain the qualifications, academic skills and knowledge necessary
            to progress on to university-level study. During the course you will learn the fundamental factors 
            of business to enable you to go on to study teaching and social work. This course is studied full-time over one year.
            You will be required to attend college lectures and seminars for a minimum of two and a half days a week. 
            You will also need to dedicate some time to self-study and research.
        </center>
    </p>
    <p></p>
    <h2><center>Course Content</center></h2>
    <p>
        <center>
            Modules on this course include: marketing, planning, strategy, 
            operations, business environment, human resources, finance and IT to prepare you for university study.
        </center>
    </p>
    <p></p>
    <h2><center>Entry Requirements</center></h2>
    <p>
        You will need Grade C/4 GCSE English and minimum Grade D/3* GCSE Maths. 
        *If applicants have Grade D/3 you will be required to sit GCSE Maths alongside your studies. 
        You will also have an interview and maths and English test. Any and all relevant work experience 
        will also be taken in to consideration.
    </p>
